<tr><td>

<a href="./overview.html">
<img src="../../images/overviewsplash.gif" border=0 alt="button"></a><td rowspan=6><b>








         <br>
Enova is a holding company. Its six subsidiaries include SDG&E, a utility that supplies natural gas and electricity to residential and business customers; Enova Energy Management (energy management); Enova Financial (affordable housing project investments; Enova Technologies (energy products and services development); Califia (equipment leasing); and Pacific Diversified Capital (commercial real estate).<br>
<H3>1995 Major Deals/Achievements/Set Backs</H3>A parent company was formed, Enova Corp., to separate the regulated portions of SDG&E's business from the unregulated portions.<br>
<P>SDG&E'S president and chief executive officer, Tom Page, stepped down and was named chairman of Enova.<br>
<P>SDG&E, Proxima, S.A. de C.V., and Pacific Enterprises International formed a partnership to build and operate natural gas distribution networks in Mexico.<br>
